{"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/gio\/dtlsconnection\/onacceptcertificate(flags:handler:)"]}],"sections":[],"metadata":{"externalID":"s:3GIO22DtlsConnectionProtocolPAAE19onAcceptCertificate5flags7handlerSi10GLibObject12ConnectFlagsV_SbAA0bC3RefV_AA014TLSCertificateN0VAA0oM0VtctF::SYNTHESIZED::s:3GIO14DtlsConnectionC","symbolKind":"method","title":"onAcceptCertificate(flags:handler:)","role":"symbol","modules":[{"name":"GIO"}],"roleHeading":"Instance Method","fragments":[{"text":"func","kind":"keyword"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"onAcceptCertificate","kind":"identifier"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"text":"flags","kind":"externalParam"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:10GLibObject12ConnectFlagsV","text":"ConnectFlags","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"kind":"text","text":", "},{"kind":"externalParam","text":"handler"},{"text":": (","kind":"text"},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"DtlsConnectionRef","preciseIdentifier":"s:3GIO17DtlsConnectionRefV"},{"text":", ","kind":"text"},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:3GIO17TLSCertificateRefV","text":"TLSCertificateRef","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"text":", ","kind":"text"},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:3GIO19TLSCertificateFlagsV","text":"TLSCertificateFlags","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"text":") -> ","kind":"text"},{"text":"Bool","kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:Sb"},{"kind":"text","text":") -> "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:Si","text":"Int"}],"extendedModule":"GIO"},"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Emitted during the TLS handshake after the peer certificate has"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"been received. You can examine "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"peerCert"},{"type":"text","text":"’s certification path by"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"calling "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_tls_certificate_get_issuer()"},{"text":" on it.","type":"text"}],"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"tokens":[{"kind":"attribute","text":"@discardableResult"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"func","kind":"keyword"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"onAcceptCertificate"},{"text":"(","kind":"text"},{"text":"flags","kind":"externalParam"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"ConnectFlags","preciseIdentifier":"s:10GLibObject12ConnectFlagsV"},{"text":" = ConnectFlags(0), ","kind":"text"},{"text":"handler","kind":"externalParam"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"keyword","text":"@escaping"},{"text":" (","kind":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/DtlsConnectionRef","preciseIdentifier":"s:3GIO17DtlsConnectionRefV","kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"DtlsConnectionRef"},{"text":", ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:3GIO17TLSCertificateRefV","text":"TLSCertificateRef","identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/TLSCertificateRef"},{"kind":"text","text":", "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/TLSCertificateFlags","preciseIdentifier":"s:3GIO19TLSCertificateFlagsV","text":"TLSCertificateFlags"},{"text":") -> ","kind":"text"},{"text":"Bool","preciseIdentifier":"s:Sb","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"kind":"text","text":") -> "},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:Si","text":"Int","kind":"typeIdentifier"}],"languages":["swift"],"platforms":["macOS"]}]},{"kind":"parameters","parameters":[{"name":"flags","content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Flags"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"","type":"text"},{"code":"true","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" to accept "},{"code":"peerCert","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" (which will also immediately end the signal emission). ","type":"text"},{"code":"false","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" to allow the signal emission to continue, which will cause the handshake to fail if no one else overrides it."},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"Run the given callback whenever the ","type":"text"},{"code":"acceptCertificate","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" signal is emitted","type":"text"}]}],"name":"handler"}]},{"kind":"content","content":[{"level":2,"type":"heading","text":"Discussion","anchor":"discussion"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"For a client-side connection, ","type":"text"},{"code":"peerCert","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" is the server’s"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"certificate, and the signal will only be emitted if the"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"certificate was not acceptable according to "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"conn"},{"type":"text","text":"’s"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/DtlsClientConnection","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":". If you would like the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"certificate to be accepted despite ","type":"text"},{"code":"errors","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":", return "},{"code":"true","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" from the","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"signal handler. Otherwise, if no handler accepts the certificate,","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"the handshake will fail with "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"badCertificate"},{"type":"text","text":"."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"GLib guarantees that if certificate verification fails, this signal"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"will be emitted with at least one error will be set in ","type":"text"},{"code":"errors","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":", but"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"it does not guarantee that all possible errors will be set."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"Accordingly, you may not safely decide to ignore any particular","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"type of error. For example, it would be incorrect to ignore"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"expired"},{"text":" if you want to allow expired","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"certificates, because this could potentially be the only error flag","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"set even if other problems exist with the certificate.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"For a server-side connection, "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"peerCert"},{"text":" is the certificate","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"presented by the client, if this was requested via the server’s"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/DtlsServerConnection","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":". On the server side,"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the signal is always emitted when the client presents a"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"certificate, and the certificate will only be accepted if a","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"handler returns ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"true"},{"text":".","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Note that if this signal is emitted as part of asynchronous I\/O"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"in the main thread, then you should not attempt to interact with","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"the user before returning from the signal handler. If you want to","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"let the user decide whether or not to accept the certificate, you","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"would have to return "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"false"},{"text":" from the signal handler on the first","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"attempt, and then after the connection attempt returns a","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"badCertificate"},{"type":"text","text":", you can interact with the user, and"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"if the user decides to accept the certificate, remember that fact,"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"create a new connection, and return "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"true"},{"text":" from the signal handler","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"the next time.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"If you are doing I\/O in another thread, you do not"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"need to worry about this, and can simply block in the signal","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"handler until the UI thread returns an answer."}]},{"type":"aside","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"This represents the underlying "},{"code":"accept-certificate","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" signal"}]}],"style":"note","name":"Note"}]}],"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/DtlsConnection\/onAcceptCertificate(flags:handler:)"},"schemaVersion":{"patch":0,"major":0,"minor":3},"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO","doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/DtlsConnection","doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/DtlsConnection\/DtlsConnectionProtocol-Implementations"]]},"kind":"symbol","references":{"doc://GIO/documentation/GIO/DtlsConnection":{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/DtlsConnection","type":"topic","kind":"symbol","role":"symbol","fragments":[{"text":"class","kind":"keyword"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"DtlsConnection","kind":"identifier"}],"navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"DtlsConnection"}],"abstract":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GDtlsConnection"},{"type":"text","text":" is the base DTLS connection class type, which wraps"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"a [iface","type":"text"},